one_reviews_text: Really liked it.  It made me interested in going to Yosemite.  My only other comments are that I wish the visuals looked crisper and I wish we saw some of the other famous scenes at the park, including the Geysers and other cool things like that.  Other than that it was great and love hearing Obama <3
I would have loved to have seen what this has to offer, but it doesn't run on my Rift S. It immediately crashes upon launching the app, with no error message or feedback.

A great feeling of being there with a great man.

review_title: Amazing! But when will it be on the Go??
one_reviews_text:
This is incredible to view on my Rift, but until it comes to Go, I can't easily share it with family/friends from my home PC VR setup.. The Tour of the Whitehouse is on the Oculus Go, and that works great, my family loved seeing that! And they really want to see this one too, but I can't bring my Rift places..
PLEASE release an Oculus Go version ASAP! (I think it used to be available in some app on Go, but the internal link stopped working and was eventually removed. This should really be it's own App download, like the whitehouse tour!)
review_feedback: Through the Ages is coming soon to the Go 👀Keep an eye out!

one_reviews_text:
I have NOW installed a CLEAN NEW ORIG.  Win 10.

I am pleased to report that it ran almost faultlessly all the way through, including credits start to finish, with several exits to set view !!!

As a scenery view diorama it is very pritty.  As long as you have an attention span greater than a goldfish, you should not be dissapointed with the "Movie" content.

Makes me want to go see it.

However Dont confuse your Win 10 crashes with problems in this app.

I shall be recommending it.

one_reviews_text: Very well done, interesting, beutifull and moving. I liked the 3D/360 technology.

Going in you have to understand this format isn’t always crystal clear, but what is clear is the passion and respect it takes to preserve our National Parks for future generations. Take a tour of Yosemite and drink in the natural beauty that will leave you awestruck. I know they won’t read this, but it was gracious of the President to take time and for his family to give him the time away from them for filming. We need more of this in VR to educate people who may never get to visit a park as to why they are so important.
Title is not launching. It starts up for a second then just goes back to the home screen for oculus as if it was never launched.  Any fix?
Excellent information about national parks.
The video quality is pretty bad but that could also be due to the limitation of the rift headset. The content is mediocre at best.

I personally don't like Obama. But this video was amazing. It was beautiful and all around great to watch. Its about a 15 minute video, its relaxing, and its great to see Yosemite. I've never been there, so it was like I was actually there with Obama

As good as any 360 video I've seen.  A bit dissapointed in the video quality of all 360 videos I've seen. Guess I have to wait a few years for 360 cameras to evolve before the videos look like my Blu-Ray 3D movies look on an HMD

If you want to experience some of the best real life VR i've seen to date watch this. Even if you don't like Obama, doesn't mean you need to skip the beauty of one of of this great American national park.
I enjoyed it and, at times, it really does give you a sense you were there. Very nicely done. I'd love to see more of this kind of thing in the future.

It crashes for me on two different computers. However, I found a work around. The player used in The People's House does work. If you copy/move the files from Oculus\Software\felix-and-paul-studios-through-the-ages-president-obama-and-the-national-parks-centennial-rift\nps\.Data\fnps\downloaded\Oculus\nps to Oculus\Software\felix-and-paul-studios-the-people-s-house-rift\who\.Data\fnps\downloaded\Oculus\who and rename nps.mp4 to who.mp4 and nps.fpxp to who.fpxp and then launch The People's House from Home it will play this National Parks video.
Our best president in a generation reminds us of the amazing gift we has a citizens: our stunning national parks. I hope we don't do anything to jeopardize these invaluable land in the next 4 years.
Great video. 3D, 360 for anyone wondering. Would love to see more VR tourist stuff like this.
Beautiful! Donald never would do something beautiful like this! Thanks to the Obamas!

A really great showcase of the possibility of VR for tourism and to help discover wonders of real world. Regarding the commentators lamenting the presence of former President Obama, don't worry you'll surely get your Mar-a-Lago video soon enough

But If you have a brain it will work and you will like it greatly. If you don't have a brain, it won't work for you and you will blame Obama and give it 1 star. 

Hint: Get the peoples house. Also very good. Swap data folders and your set. If you hate Obama and really want to see how bad he screwed this up, you should delete you system32.dll file from your computer. That should fix it.

Got this to work by following the tips here and copying the data to the Peoples House player. Well worth the effort as there's some stunning views, just wish they lasted a bit longer to take it all in.

review_title: Amazing - I need to go to Yellowstone!
one_reviews_text: This video is amazing, the scenes, the landscape, the mountains and the water, the message is clear, go see these national parks. Enjoy what our planet has to offer and be one with mother nature! I'm definetly going on holiday here with my wife and daughter! :)

Very educational and informative.  The landscapes and 3D visual creativity was excellent.  I gave it a 4 because it was a little slow at some points and started to lose my attention.  Overall good educational video.

I really enjoyed The Peoples House video, as well as all others I have seen from Felix and Paul studios, but this one won't work at all.  I initially tried it on an overclocked 2550K processor and a 1080 Founders, and assumed that it wouldn't launch due to absent hardware for transcoding, but after purchasing a 7700K and trying it again, it still wont work.  It is sad... The People's House is one of the most awe inspiring VR videos I have seen, and I would love to watch this one as well, but it doesn't seem like it's going to happen.  I have written the developer about the problems many of us are having, and hope that they will figure out a solution, because the concept seems to good to miss out on.
The scenes are beautiful, audio clear and well done, message on point. Free! What's not to love??

It has been like this for over a month now..Felix & Paul Studios need to pull there finger out and fix this and ill change it to the 5 stars it deserves.

This is less a VR experience than a bunch of scenes shot with 360 degree VR cams.  It's not ultra-HD yet, but you can still witness the grandeur of Yosemite if you've never been there yourself.  Whatever your politics, leave it at the door and just enjoy the experience of what its like to stand a few feet from a U.S. president without Secret Service agents and crowds.  Just the tranquil setting of one of America's greatest treasures.
Requires additional in-app download. Once in, this is a great VR mini-tour of Yosemite National Park, guided, in-part, by POTUS number 44.
